Gemini said






*Unified Earnings View, Reports and Gamified Rider Experience*










We are excited to introduce an upgrade for Earning and Incentives, which
will not only make admins' lives easier but also make riders earn more!



This update connects everything, bringing better data to administrators and
a much smoother app experience to riders.


Why We Built This?














Before this update, tracking rider earnings and incentives was fragmented.
Managers had to manually patch together separate pieces of information to
check payouts. We built this new tool to:

   -

   Stop payout confusion by putting earnings and incentives in one place.
   -

   Easier to map rider earnings, incentives, performance metrics, track
   productivity, control costs, plus evaluate the effectiveness of incentiv=
e
   programs through reports.
   -

   Made earning more fun by making it more engaging and ultimately
   motivating riders to reach the next level.

What=E2=80=99s New!



*Combined View*Data for Earnings, Order Earnings, and Incentives already
exists, but is scattered across different sections. Penalties are managed
separately and has been integrated in the unified payout. All this falling
under one umbrella will be now falling under one view.





*Earning and Incentives Report*


Admins can now create reports on daily summaries, day-level earnings, and
incentive effectiveness metrics to help track rider productivity and
optimize payout costs.


The feature aims to eliminate visibility gaps by providing real-time
analytics on rider earnings, incentives, and performance metrics.






*Rider Incentive gamified version*


At its core, the purpose of gamification is to *increase engagement,
motivation, and participation*. By doing this we are encouraging riders to
do more and earn more!


What This Means To You






   1.

   *Eliminates Fragmentation:* Consolidates scattered data (earnings,
   incentives, penalties) into a single view, completely removing manual
   tracking and payout confusion for managers.


   2.

   *Optimizes Costs:* Provides clear reports on daily summaries and
   incentive effectiveness, making it easy to track rider productivity and
   manage payout budgets.


   3.

   *Boosts Motivation:* Uses a gamified approach to transform a standard
   routine into an engaging experience that inspires riders to reach higher
   milestones.

What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
